{"coursehistories": {"path": "/coursehistories/2026"}, "description": "Forensic mental health is the interface between the law and mental health. This course examines the components of human behavior that bring people into a judicial setting. Content will cover: criminal personalities, forensic interview, and the role of forensic psychiatry. Domestic violence offenders, sex offenders, stalkers, gang members, and offenders who commit homicide will be discussed. Definitions and dynamics of criminal motherhood and the psychodynamics of violent juvenile offenders will be presented. Use of the internet by offenders will also be discussed. This course also offers a field experience in which student's interview incarcerated individuals. \n\n", "semester": "2008C", "name": "FORENSIC MENTAL HEALTH", "reviews": {"path": "/courses/19078/reviews", "values": [{"ratings": {"rAmountLearned": "2.38", "rDifficulty": "1.61", "rStimulateInterest": "2.69", "rRecommendMajor": "2.84", "rCourseQuality": "2.57", "rWorkRequired": "1.50", "rInstructorAccess": "2.98", "rReadingsValue": "1.87", "rRecommendNonMajor": "2.82", "rCommAbility": "2.92", "rInstructorQuality": "2.92"}, "section": {"name": "FORENSIC MENTAL HEALTH", "sectionnum": "401", "primary_alias": "NURS-531-401", "path": "/courses/19078/sections/401", "id": "19078-401", "aliases": ["NURS-531-401", "NURS-331-401"]}, "comments": "", "num_students": 152, "path": "/courses/19078/sections/401/reviews/885-KATHLEEN-M-BROWN", "instructor": {"path": "/instructors/885-KATHLEEN-M-BROWN", "first_name": "KATHLEEN M", "last_name": "BROWN", "id": "885-KATHLEEN-M-BROWN", "name": "KATHLEEN M BROWN"}, "num_reviewers": 62, "id": "19078-401-885-KATHLEEN-M-BROWN"}, {"ratings": {"rAmountLearned": "2.38", "rDifficulty": "1.61", "rStimulateInterest": "2.30", "rRecommendMajor": "2.84", "rCourseQuality": "2.57", "rWorkRequired": "1.50", "rInstructorAccess": "2.49", "rReadingsValue": "1.87", "rRecommendNonMajor": "2.82", "rCommAbility": "2.35", "rInstructor